    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That makes sense, especially with the tobacco economy. I'm also seeing some specific clusters in the records where entire households seem to just... vanish or appear in very small, concentrated pockets that don't quite match the surrounding rural spread. Is there any specific historical phenomenon, like internal displacement or maybe even undocumented migration, that could explain those weirdly tight clusters of people appearing out of nowhere?",
